Polymorphism.

Inheritance gives us polymorphism, which is one of the most important ideas in object oriented programming. Because Dog is a kind of Animal, a variable of type Animal can hold a Dog. When you call the speak method on that variable, the java virtual machine dispatches to the actual runtime type's version of the method. So if you have a list of Animal, and some of them are Dog instances, the loop that calls speak on each one will see Dog dot speak run for the Dog instances, even though your loop was written against the Animal type. This is exactly how frameworks like Spring let you swap implementations without changing the calling code. You program against an interface or a base class. Spring injects the actual implementation at runtime. Polymorphism is what makes this seamless.
